Bill Gates is an American business magnate, software developer, philanthropist, and co-founder of Microsoft Corporation. He was born on October 28, 1955. Gates played a key role in the personal computer revolution by developing and leading Microsoft, which became one of the world's largest and most influential technology companies. Besides his business achievements, he is also known for his philanthropic work through the Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation, focusing on global health, education, and poverty alleviation.
